<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A6EF515F-4796-49CC-AB48-E71F5CCE0E51" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A6EF515F-4796-49CC-AB48-E71F5CCE0E51" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b translate="no" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 5931: The media is not smooth, white, opaque enough (scanner not calibrated) (new)</b> </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-13B8358D-3B91-4CA1-9D8B-2000EA737F70"><p class="- topic/p ">The media is not smooth, white, opaque enough. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The measurement for checking whether the media is smooth, white, opaque enough for calibrations has determined that the scan of the media does not meet the criteria. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In this case the suspect is that the scanner is not calibrated. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-6FAF1E2F-6024-4F2F-A6E3-410694AA905F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Collect</b> </title><p class="- topic/p "><u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step 
</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is the calibration step: “MediumSmoothWhiteOpaqueCheck” which is part of one the following calibration sequences 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Media calibrations 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Printhead calibration 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Carriage calibration 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p "><u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print 
</u> 
</p><table id="GUID-823138FA-C0BA-48A6-BC4A-FA4958E2A0B2" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">C1640/C1650 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">No patterns are printed 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">C1630/CMxx 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">No patterns are printed 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-C9636EF4-881C-4A1D-9D6C-BDA5D19FB41B" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyse/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-3E1BC7AD-FDE9-441F-932F-830C32103FFC" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-12D29AD0-4255-4C38-850A-FF4635667193-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-12D29AD0-4255-4C38-850A-FF4635667193-svg.svg"/></fig><table id="GUID-16B13F78-2644-46CA-8EEB-E4B599601425" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">ToDo 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the correct media thickness is set in the RIP 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Adjust the media-thickness in the RIP 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the media is flat on the platen (print surface) : No bulging. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Adjust vacuum setting in the RIP 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the used media is white, smooth and opaque. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> This calibration can only be executed on white, smooth and opaque media. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check whether the M&amp;C-scanner needs to be cleaned 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Clean the glass-window of the M&amp;C-scanner using IPA. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Calibrate the M&amp;C-scanner 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1.<xref href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref>:Select M&amp;C scanner 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">2.<xref href="GUID-B828E436-A124-4809-981E-2DBE1E09A388.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Replace M&amp;C-scanner 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="GUID-563F9EBE-CC03-4CAA-93C8-8AA3AB9B162B.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>05 How to remove the Measurement &amp; Control (M&amp;C) unit</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3BF9636D-78E1-4CC1-BC18-26C801582612" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases this calibration fails due to polluted or incorrect media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The contrast of the media in respect to the printed markers should be large enough. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Secondly maintaining the printer by doing regular cleaning will also minimises the change of failing calibrations. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-ECC32056-E331-45C8-901D-6A32C6E5E8AC" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">The media (used for calibrations) is checked whether its suitable for the calibrations. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For instance, when "AutodisableNozzles" (Part of the nozzle optimalisation) is performed on structured media the results will be very bad, and many nozzles will be flagged as non-jetting. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As not all customers are aware of this requirement this calibration-step is present for all calibrations which can be started from the UI. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-480B4E14-7AB9-4230-BBE2-97A999EC3E19.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
